FBIS3-54080 "drnes015_j_94009" FBIS-NES-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Saudi Arabia King Fahd Sends Condolences to Syria's al-Asad LD2101201894 Riyadh SPA in English 1942 GMT 21 Jan 94 LD2101201894 Riyadh SPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Riyadh, Jan 21, SPA -- The Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz condoled, in a telephone call, Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad over the sad demise of his eldest son Basil al-Asad. King Fahd prayed to Allah almighty to bestow his mercy on the deceased and to grant his bereaved family patience and solace. Basil, 31, an army major, engineer and parachutist, died on Friday in a car crash.
